column4: Yep. We did. Even though we shouldn't have.
Oh no, I forgot to buy an After Pill! What now?
Ugh... Looks like I will have to accept that she might get pregnant.
I want you to take the pill.""
I was hoping you'd say that. I was so worried. I thought about it a lot last night.
What'd I do if you asked me to raise a child? Things are already bad enough for me alone as they are.
I wouldn't want to make our child suffer through my misfortune.
Especially since we're still students. Our child would have gone through so much pain.
Let's have lots of kids when we're both proper adults, okay? Let's make a big family together.

column5: I want you to have the baby.""

column4: Raising a baby is a lot of work, you know?
We're still students. There's also my misfortune, which might affect us and our child…
I'll take full responsibility, don't worry.
…I'm so happy. I trust you, [Pあだ名]. So okay, I'll have the child if I get pregnant. I know you'll be there for us.
As long as you're there, everything will be alright, I'm sure.
